lead_paragraph: SIOUX CITY, Iowa — With five days until the Iowa caucuses, Joe Biden is fending off a new onslaught of GOP attacks over his son's business overseas and facing piling pressure to show Democratic voters he can handle the incoming.
headline_main: Biden Under Pressure to Prove He Can Thwart New GOP Attacks
headline_print_headline: Biden Under Pressure to Prove He Can Thwart New GOP Attacks

abstract: With more than 15,000 people killed by gun violence in the United States last year - not counting suicides - Democrats running for their party's presidential nomination are pointing to inaction in Washington as evidence they should be chosen to run against Republican President Donald Trump.
snippet: With more than 15,000 people killed by gun violence in the United States last year - not counting suicides - Democrats running for their party's presidential nomination are pointing to inaction in Washington as evidence they should be chosen to ru...
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - With more than 15,000 people killed by gun violence in the United States last year - not counting suicides - Democrats running for their party's presidential nomination are pointing to inaction in Washington as evidence they should be chosen to run against Republican President Donald Trump.
headline_main: Background Checks and Bump Stock Bans: 2020 Democrats on Gun Control
headline_print_headline: Background Checks and Bump Stock Bans: 2020 Democrats on Gun Control

abstract: The Democratic contenders hoping to challenge President Donald Trump in November 2020 all argue the Republican leader's unorthodox foreign policy approach has endangered American interests.

lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - The Democratic contenders hoping to challenge President Donald Trump in November 2020 all argue the Republican leader's unorthodox foreign policy approach has endangered American interests.
headline_main: Where the 2020 Democratic Presidential Hopefuls Differ on Foreign Policy
headline_print_headline: Where the 2020 Democratic Presidential Hopefuls Differ on Foreign Policy

abstract: In the final days before the caucuses, Ms. Warren is taking on the electability question in ads, on the stump and on her campaign bus, urging voters to embrace “courage over cynicism” and “hope over fear.”
snippet: In the final days before the caucuses, Ms. Warren is taking on the electability question in ads, on the stump and on her campaign bus, urging voters to embrace “courage over cynicism” and “hope over fear.”
lead_paragraph: CEDAR RAPIDS, Iowa — The last time Senator Elizabeth Warren trundled across Iowa in a specially decorated campaign vehicle, an R.V. headed to the Iowa State Fair in August, it was wrapped with a cheeky play on the slogan for her sweeping agenda: “Honk if you’re ready for big, structural change!”
